{"SPECIAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a species; constituting a species or sort.","pos":""},{"def":"Particular; peculiar; different from others; extraordinary; uncommon.","pos":""}],"SPECIALISM":[{"def":"Devotion to a particular and restricted part or branch of knowledge, art, or science; as, medical specialism.","pos":""}],"SPECIALIST":[{"def":"One who devotes himself to some specialty; as, a medical specialist, one who devotes himself to diseases of particular parts of the body, as the eye, the ear, the nerves, etc.","pos":""}],"SPECIALITY":[{"def":"See Specialty, 3.","pos":""}],"SPECIALIZATION":[{"def":"The setting spart of a particular organ for the performance of a particular function.","pos":""}],"SPECIALIZE":[{"def":"To supply with an organ or organs having a special function or functions.","pos":""}],"SPECIALLY":[{"def":"In a special manner; partcularly; especially.","pos":""},{"def":"For a particular purpose; as, a meeting of the legislature is specially summoned.","pos":""}],"SPECIALTY":[{"def":"A contract or obligation under seal; a contract by deed; a writing, under seal, given as security for a debt particularly specified.","pos":""}],"SPECIE":[{"def":"Spe\"ci*e, Defn: abl.","pos":""}],"SPECIES":[{"def":"A group of individuals agreeing in common attributes, and designated by a common name; a conception subordinated to another conception, called a genus, or generic conception, from which it differs in containing or comprehending more attributes, and extending to fewer individuals.","pos":""},{"def":"The form or shape given to materials; fashion or shape; form; figure.","pos":""}],"SPECIFIABLE":[{"def":"Admitting specification; capable of being specified.","pos":""}],"SPECIFIC":[{"def":"Exerting a peculiar influence over any part of the body; preventing or curing disease by a peculiar adaption, and not on general principles; as, quinine is a specific medicine in cases of malaria.","pos":""}],"SPECIFICALLY":[{"def":"In a specific manner.","pos":""}],"SPECIFICALNESS":[{"def":"The quality of being specific.","pos":""}],"SPECIFICATE":[{"def":"To show, mark, or designate the species, or the distinguishing particulars of; to specify.","pos":""}],"SPECIFICATION":[{"def":"The act of specifying or determining by a mark or limit; notation of limits.","pos":""},{"def":"The designation of particulars; particular mention; as, the specification of a charge against an officer.","pos":""}],"SPECIFICNESS":[{"def":"The quality or state of being specific.","pos":""}],"SPECIFY":[{"def":"To mention or name, as a particular thing; to designate in words so as to distinguish from other things; as, to specify the uses of a plant; to specify articles purchased.","pos":""}],"SPECIMEN":[{"def":"A part, or small portion, of anything, or one of a number of things, intended to exhibit the kind and quality of the whole, or of what is not exhibited; a sample; as, a specimen of a man's handwriting; a specimen of painting; aspecimen of one's art.","pos":""}],"SPECIOSITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being specious; speciousness.","pos":""},{"def":"That which is specious.","pos":""}],"SPECIOUS":[{"def":"Presenting a pleasing appearance; pleasing in form or look; showy.","pos":""},{"def":"Apparently right; superficially fair, just, or correct, but not so in reality; appearing well at first view; plausible; as, specious reasoning; a specious argument.","pos":""}],"SPECK":[{"def":"The blubber of whales or other marine mammals; also, the fat of the hippopotamus.","pos":""}],"SPECKLE":[{"def":"A little or spot in or anything, of a different substance or color from that of the thing itself.","pos":""}],"SPECKLED":[{"def":"Marked or variegated with small spots of a different color from that of the rest of the surface.","pos":""}],"SPECKLED-BILL":[{"def":"The American white-fronted goose (Anser albifrons).","pos":""}],"SPECKLEDNESS":[{"def":"The quality of being speckled.","pos":""}],"SPECKSIONEER":[{"def":"The chief harpooner, who also directs in cutting up the speck, or blubber; -- so called among whalers.","pos":""}],"SPECTACLE":[{"def":"An optical instrument consisting of two lenses set in a light frame, and worn to assist sight, to obviate some defect in the organs of vision, or to shield the eyes from bright light.","pos":""}],"SPECTACLED":[{"def":"Having the eyes surrounded by color markings, or patches of naked skin, resembling spectacles.","pos":""}],"SPECTACULAR":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a shows; of the nature of a show.","pos":""},{"def":"Adapted to excite wonder and admiration by a display of pomp or of scenic effects; as, a spectacular celebration of some event; a spectacular play.","pos":""}],"SPECTANT":[{"def":"Looking forward.","pos":""}],"SPECTATION":[{"def":"Regard; aspect; appearance.","pos":""}],"SPECTATOR":[{"def":"One who on; one who sees or beholds; a beholder; one who is personally present at, and sees, any exhibition; as, the spectators at a show.","pos":""}],"SPECTATORIAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a spectator.","pos":""}],"SPECTATORSHIP":[{"def":"A female beholder or looker-on.","pos":""}],"SPECTIONEER":[{"def":"Same as Specsioneer.","pos":""}],"SPECTRAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the spectrum; made by the spectrum; as, spectral colors; spectral analysis.","pos":""}],"SPECTRALLY":[{"def":"In the form or manner of a specter.","pos":""}],"SPECTROBOLOMETER":[{"def":"A combination of spectroscope and bolometer for determining the distribution of energy in a spectrum.","pos":""}],"SPECTROELECTRIC":[{"def":"Spec`tro*e*lec\"tric, a.","pos":""}],"SPECTROGRAM":[{"def":"A photograph, map, or diagram of a spectrum.","pos":""}],"SPECTROHELIOGRAM":[{"def":"A photograph of the sun made by monochromatic light, usually of the calcium line (k), and showing the sun's faculæ and prominences.","pos":""}],"SPECTROHELIOGRAPH":[{"def":"An apparatus for making spectroheliograms, consisting of a spectroscopic camera used in combination with a telescope, and provided with clockwork for moving the sun's image across the slit.","pos":""}],"SPECTROLOGICAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to spectrology; as, spectrological studies or experiments.","pos":""}],"SPECTROLOGY":[{"def":"The science of spectrum analysis in any or all of its relations and applications.","pos":""}],"SPECTROMETER":[{"def":"A spectroscope fitted for measurements of the luminious spectra observed with it.","pos":""}],"SPECTROMETRY":[{"def":"Art or process of using the spectrometer, or of measuring wave lengths of rays of a spectrum.","pos":""}],"SPECTROPHONE":[{"def":"An instrument constructed on the principle of the photophone and used in spectrum analysis as an adjunct to the spectroscope.","pos":""}],"SPECTROPHOTOMETER":[{"def":"An instrument for measuring or comparing the intensites of the colors of the spectrum.","pos":""}],"SPECTROPHOTOMETRY":[{"def":"The art of comparing, photometrically, the brightness of two spectra, wave length by wave length; the use of the spectrophotometer.","pos":""}],"SPECTROSCOPE":[{"def":"An optical instrument for forming and examining spectra (as that of solar light, or those produced by flames in which different substances are volatilized), so as to determine, from the position of the spectral lines, the composition of the substance.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to a spectroscope, or spectroscopy.","pos":""}],"SPECTROSCOPIST":[{"def":"One who investigates by means of a spectroscope; one skilled in the use of the spectroscope.","pos":""}],"SPECTROSCOPY":[{"def":"The use of the spectroscope; investigations made with the spectroscope.","pos":""}],"SPECTRUM":[{"def":"An apparition; a specter.","pos":""}],"SPECULAR":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to a speculum; conducted with the aid of a speculum; as, a specular examination.","pos":""}],"SPECULATE":[{"def":"To view subjects from certain premises given or assumed, and infer conclusions respecting them a priori.","pos":""},{"def":"To purchase with the expectation of a contingent advance in value, and a consequent sale at a profit; -- often, in a somewhat depreciative sense, of unsound or hazardous transactions; as, to speculate in coffee, in sugar, or in bank stock.","pos":""}],"SPECULATION":[{"def":"The act or process of reasoning a priori from premises given or assumed.","pos":""}],"SPECULATIST":[{"def":"One who speculates, or forms theories; a speculator; a theorist.","pos":""}],"SPECULATIVE":[{"def":"Given to speculation; contemplative.","pos":""},{"def":"Involving, or formed by, speculation; ideal; theoretical; not established by demonstration.","pos":""}],"SPECULATOR":[{"def":"One who speculates.","pos":""},{"def":"One who engages in speculation; one who buys and sells goods, land, etc.","pos":""}],"SPECULATORIAL":[{"def":"Speculatory; speculative.","pos":""}],"SPECULATORY":[{"def":"Intended or adapted for viewing or espying; having oversight.","pos":""},{"def":"Exercising speculation; speculative.","pos":""}],"SPECULIST":[{"def":"One who observes or considers; an observer.","pos":""}],"SPECULUM":[{"def":"An instrument for dilating certain passages of the body, and throwing light within them, thus facilitating examination or surgical operations.","pos":""},{"def":"A bright and lustrous patch of color found on the wings of ducks and some other birds.","pos":""}]}